1â†’| `TransportClosedError`            | Transport has been closed (during shutdown).                                               |\n   622â†’| `AllTransportsFailedError`        | All transports in a fallback chain failed.                                                 |\n   623â†’| `TransportSendError`              | Failed to send a message through the transport.                                            |\n   624â†’| `DelayedMessagesNotSupportedError`| Delayed messages requested but transport doesn't support them.                             |\n   625â†’| `EventNotRegisteredError`         | Event type is not registered in the schema.                                                |\n   626â†’| `SubscriberNotRegisteredError`    | Subscriber is not registered for this event.                                               |\n   627â†’| `NoSubscribersExistError`         | Event has no subscribers registered.                                                       |\n   628â†’| `InvalidSchemaError`              | Schema configuration is invalid.                                                           |\n   629â†’| `SubscriberIsStubError`           | A SubscriberStub was registered in a consuming schema.                                     |\n   630â†’| `LocalTransportCannotProcessStubError` | LocalTransport cannot process events for SubscriberStubs.                             |\n   631â†’| `QueueNotFoundError`              | Queue does not exist or has not been created.                                              |\n   632â†’| `InvalidEventError`               | Event is invalid or missing required fields.                                               |\n   633â†’| `MessageMaybePoisonedError`       | Message redelivered too many times (possible poison message).                              |\n   634â†’| `IdempotentMessageCannotRetryError` | Non-idempotent subscriber received a redelivered message.                                |\n   635â†’| `TimeoutError`                    | Operation timed out before completing.                                                     |\n   636â†’\n   637â†’**Retry Control Errors** (thrown by subscribers to control retry behavior):\n   638â†’\n   639â†’| Error                | Description                                                                                    |\n   640â†’| -------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n   641â†’| `DoRetry`            | Forces retry regardless of subscriber idempotency setting.                                     |\n   642â†’| `DontRetry`          | Prevents retry regardless of subscriber idempotency setting. Message goes to dead-letter.      |\n   643â†’| `EventAssertionError`| Assertion error that should never be retried. Goes directly to dead-letter queue.              |\n   644â†’\n   645â†’# Other features\n   646â†’\n   647â†’### `universalMetadata`\n   648â†’\n   649â†’It is often the case that you want every event to have a consistent set of metadata.\n   650â†’**Matador** provides a hook `loadUniversalMetadata` which you can use to do this.\n   651â†’\n   652â†’You can combine this with `asyncLocalStorage` to set session based metadata on your events.\n   653â†’\n   654â†’Here is a real world example:\n   655â†’\n   656â†’```ts\n   657â†’loadUniversalMetadata: () => {\n   658â†’  const store = asyncLocalStorage?.getStore()\n   659â†’  return {\n   660â†’    timestamp: new Date(),\n   661â†’    correlationId: store?.correlationId || null,\n   662â†’    userId: store?.userId || null,\n   663â†’  }\n   664â†’},\n   665â†’```\n   666â†’\n   667â†’### Schema plugins\n   668â†’\n   669â†’Sometimes, you want to run a subscriber on every event in your _schema_.\n   670â†’Instead of defining the subscriber mapping for every event, you can use `installPlugins` to add global subscribers:\n   671â†’\n   672â†’```ts\n   673â†’import { installPlugins } from '@meetsmore/matador-v2';\n   674â†’\n   675â†’const baseSchema: MatadorSchema = {\n   676â†’  [UserCreatedEvent.key]: [UserCreatedEvent, [sendWelcomeEmail]],\n   677â†’  [OrderPlacedEvent.key]: [OrderPlacedEvent, [processOrder]],\n   678â†’  [ChatMessageSentEvent.key]: [ChatMessageSentEvent, [notifyRecipient]],\n   679â†’};\n   680â†’\n   681â†’const myMatadorSchema = installPlugins(baseSchema, [\n   682â†’  {\n   683â†’    subscriber: logToBigQuery,\n   684â†’    exclusions: [ChatMessageSentEvent.key], // Don't log chat messages\n   685â†’  }\n   686â†’]);\n   687â†’```\n   688â†’\n   689â†’Each plugin defines a `subscriber` and optional `exclusions` array of event keys to skip.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n",
